I understand that yoga comes with philosophy, and that's fine (as long as it's common sense.) But using the term "third eye" is from an altogether different scope. It's from Hinduism and is part of their religion. Now, I'm not a Hinduist (as well as many people practicing here) and don't believe in third eye concept. I don't see why it has to included in the yoga practice. Surely, there are many alternative words that could make sense to everyone, not just a small hinduistic group.
